---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Read the Urban Harvest Lab privacy policy covering analytics, email communication, affiliate links, and user enquiries."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-policy/"
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero__panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">Privacy policy</span>
        <h1>How visitor data and communication are handled.</h1>
        <p>
          This policy is written for a content website. It covers common scenarios such as analytics, email enquiries,
          affiliate links, and future newsletter functionality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container info-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Information collected</span>
        <h2>Basic site usage data</h2>
        <p>
          The site may collect standard analytics information such as page views, referrers, device categories, and
          browser information in order to understand site performance and improve content.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Direct contact</span>
        <h2>Email correspondence</h2>
        <p>
          If you contact Urban Harvest Lab directly, your email address and the contents of your message may be retained
          for the purpose of responding and maintaining a record of the conversation.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Affiliate links</span>
        <h2>Third-party destinations</h2>
        <p>
          Some outbound links may go to third-party retailers or partners. Those websites operate under their own
          privacy policies and terms.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Future newsletter</span>
        <h2>Email subscriptions</h2>
        <p>
          If newsletter signup is added later, subscribers should be able to opt out easily. Email delivery and storage
          would then also be subject to the privacy terms of the chosen email service provider.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
